headline: FedEx Data Push Gains Focus With New Retail Momentum Index
summary: FedEx (NYSE:FDX) and Dun & Bradstreet announced a collaboration to create the Retail Momentum Index. The Index will combine FedEx shipping data with Dun & Bradstreet business data to track U.S. retail activity in real time. The new tool is positioned as an early indicator of retail trends, ahead of traditional government reports. FedEx is best known for its global shipping network. headline: InPost to return to private hands in $9.3B Advent–FedEx deal
summary: An investor group led by Advent International and FedEx has agreed to buy InPost at a €7.8 billion (about $9.3 billion) valuation in an all-cash deal—bringing the Polish parcel locker operator back into private hands five years after its Amsterdam IPO. Advent and FedEx will pay €15.60 per share for InPost—a 50% premium to its undisturbed trading price. headline: New Ownership of PostalAnnex in Boca Raton, Florida Brings Fresh Perspective on Serving the Community and Boosting Shipping and Office Services
summary: Annex Brands, Inc., a leading franchisor in the packing, shipping, and office services industries, is pleased to announce the successful transfer of ownership of an existing PostalAnnex location in Boca Raton, FL to new owners, Nestor Abad and Ynes Nero. This transition to new ownership ensures that the community will benefit from the essential shipping and office services provided by this PostalAnnex for the last three years.

headline: Shipping Is the New COGS: Carriers' 2026 Rate Hikes Are Squeezing Ecommerce Margins
summary: As UPS, FedEx, and other major carriers roll out their 2026 rate structures, the ecommerce landscape faces a critical inflection point. With headline General Rate Increases (GRIs) of 5.9% masking effective increases of 10–20% due to surcharges, shipping has ceased to be a simple operational expense. It has evolved into a core component of Cost of Goods Sold (COGS), determining whether online retailers are profitable or merely busy.
